<DOC><DOCNO> AP880329-0119 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-29-88 1312EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Ghana-Corruption     03-29 0139</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Ghana-Corruption,0144</SECOND><HEAD>33 Police Officers Fired for Corruption in Ghana Crackdown</HEAD><DATELINE>ACCRA, Ghana (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The government fired 33 police officers fordrug trafficking, armed robbery, accepting bribes and other crimesas part of a corruption crackdown, authorities said Tuesday.   Six officers were dismissed for stealing diamonds in the miningtown of Akwatia near Accra, police said. Ten others had smuggledmarijuana to neighboring Ivory Coast by boat.   Among the fired officers was a deputy police superintendent, butthere were no details on where he had been posted.   The announcement by the National Police Council, headed byGhanaian leader Flight Lt. Jerry Rawlings, did not say if theofficers had been arrested.   Two weeks ago, 19 officers were fired for armed robbery and drugtrafficking in the crackdown aimed at reducing corruption andimproving police efficiency and credibility.</TEXT></DOC>